translationBlock.key: The first argument is the entity to be held on a leash, and must be living. The second is the holder of the leash. This does not have to be living, but the only non-living entity that will persist as a holder across restarts is the leash hitch. Players, bats, enderdragons, withers and certain other entities can not be held by leashes due to minecraft limitations.
